 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","title":"robot-redesign/surfaces: rewrite digest and attention as the prioritized action queue","description":"Rewrite digest and attention so they form the heart of the ongoing operator loop rather than acting like separate vaguely-related summaries. This task exists because ntm's strongest agent-native idea is the attention feed, and the redesign should put that at the center.","design":"Digest should answer what changed since a cursor in grouped, replay-safe form, including correlated actuation outcomes, operator attention-state changes, and intentional resurfacing of previously cooled-down or snoozed issues. Attention should answer what deserves action now, with reason codes, freshness, severity, stable resource references, request or outcome correlation handles where relevant, structured next_actions or equivalent remediation descriptors, compact evidence summaries or explanation handles, explicit aggregation or suppression markers when items represent rolled-up churn rather than raw event volume, and clear indicators when an item is pinned, snoozed, acknowledged, muted, or manually escalated. The two surfaces should feel like adjacent views over the same durable state rather than unrelated features, and they should bridge cleanly into inspect and diagnostics flows when an operator needs to understand why an item is present or absent. This task is where ntm steals the derived-actionability lesson from vibe_cockpit without adopting its fleet or analytics posture.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when digest and attention are coherent, prioritized, cursor-aware surfaces that help an agent tend the system over time instead of repeatedly rescanning the entire world, while still supporting safe retries, verified outcomes, durable operator control, and a concise signal-to-noise ratio.","notes":"If agents still need to reconstruct the next action from raw dumps, the redesign has missed its main ergonomic payoff.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":240,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:17.499375794Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T08:21:00.507365232Z","closed_at":"2026-03-23T08:21:00.433229156Z","close_reason":"Completed: digest now exposes a bounded prioritized_queue in source and CLI surfaces, with ordering/cap semantics covered by focused tests and verified by clean review.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["attention","robot-redesign","surfaces"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.10","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:23:31.860408763Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.11","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:29:48.280017075Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:47:58.558445530Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:57:23.095867952Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:02:34.463848955Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.8","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:25.674213998Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.9","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:17:49.170632351Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:03.333815090Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:31.912454353Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:03.868060207Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:23:43.717946841Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:30:03.251061190Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:04.415158483Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:17.499375794Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":353,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","author":"ubuntu","text":"Sensitivity follow-up: digest and attention should preserve actionability while avoiding raw-secret churn. If an item depends on hidden evidence, the surface should carry safe previews, disclosure markers, and drill-down handles instead of dumping unsafe text.","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:37:22Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.6.4","title":"robot-redesign/surfaces: rationalize targeted inspect surfaces for session and agent drill-down","description":"Rationalize the drill-down surfaces used after bootstrap and triage for session and agent inspection. This task exists because operators need to inspect panes, agents, output, activity, context, and process state in detail, but that detail should project from the shared model instead of recreating command sprawl.","design":"The work should decide which session and agent inspect views remain distinct commands or modes, how they key into sessions, agents, and panes, how invalid or stale lookup requests are reported with machine-actionable follow-up guidance, and how they expose detail that is too verbose for snapshot, status, or attention. It should also make explicit how output, activity, context, and process detail is presented without leaking raw tmux mechanics back into the surface contract, and where these views deliberately hand off to the shared diagnostics flow when deeper why, evidence, truncation, or replay context is needed.

The goal is disciplined drill-down for session and agent state, not a generic debug dump.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when session and agent inspect surfaces are coherently defined and backed by the shared runtime projection with stable keys, detail semantics, and user-facing purpose.","notes":"A useful heuristic: a session or agent inspect surface should answer a focused follow-up question raised by snapshot or attention, not replace them.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"ubuntu","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:18.455554982Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T18:57:07.958957490Z","closed_at":"2026-03-23T18:57:07.958451052Z","close_reason":"Added projection-backed inspect-session and inspect-agent robot surfaces with root/capabilities/schema/registry wiring plus focused store-backed tests; verified via go test, go build, golangci-lint, gofmt, and goimports.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["inspect","robot-redesign","surfaces"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:47:59.118868718Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:57:23.639152818Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:02:35.037149476Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.8","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:26.396146635Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.9","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:17:49.809197082Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:04.923412198Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:05.426419999Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:32.747212478Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:05.979715370Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:18.455554982Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":332,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"This bead was narrowed intentionally so session/agent drill-down can progress independently from coordination/quota/incident drill-down. The split improves graph clarity and makes the inspect surface family more understandable for future implementers.","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:47:52Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.6.5","title":"robot-redesign/surfaces: align JSON, TOON, markdown, and terse rendering with the shared section model","description":"Align all renderer variants with the same underlying section model so format differences do not create semantic drift. This task exists because alternate renderers are valuable, but only if they remain projections of the same facts.","design":"The work should identify which sections can be faithfully rendered in JSON, TOON, markdown, and terse forms, how section omission is signaled when formats intentionally compress information, how stable ordering survives format changes, and how truncation cues, omission reasons, and compact explanation handles remain explicit instead of being hidden inside formatter-specific behavior. Renderer-specific affordances should remain subordinate to shared semantics.

This task should reduce duplicated formatting logic that currently smuggles in different ideas of what the system state is.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when alternate renderers are visibly thin projections over the shared section model and when format changes no longer imply semantic changes.","notes":"Renderer diversity is fine; semantic divergence or hidden format-specific truncation is not.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:19.443640478Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T00:11:35.498453374Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["renderers","robot-redesign","surfaces"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:57:24.180659194Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:02:35.626151138Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:19.443640478Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:32.881728949Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:33.330634468Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:33.782608292Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:34.236529813Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:48:01.942439757Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:34.895463050Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-j9jo3.6.6","title":"robot-redesign/surfaces: rationalize targeted inspect surfaces for work, coordination, quota, and incident drill-down","description":"Split the inspect-surface work so coordination-heavy drill-down does not stay entangled with session and agent drill-down. This task exists because work backlog, unread mail, reservation conflicts, handoffs, quota pressure, and incidents deserve a distinct operator-facing detail model from session/pane inspection.","design":"The work should define inspect views or modes for work items, coordination state, quota or health state, and incidents, including stable lookup keys, expected detail depth, how invalid or unsupported lookups are reported, and how these views are reached from snapshot and attention. It should also make clear where these detail surfaces stop, how they coordinate with the shared diagnostics flow for evidence, source-health causes, cursor or replay context, and incident reasoning, and why they do not become another dumping ground for raw subsystem output.

This task intentionally complements the session or agent inspect task instead of replacing it.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when work, coordination, quota, and incident drill-down are coherently defined and backed by the shared runtime projection with stable semantics and focused operator value.","notes":"These inspect surfaces should explain coordination pain and remediation options, not merely restate the summary sections in a more verbose format.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"ubuntu","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:47:44.351219027Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T18:57:24.599638307Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["inspect","robot-redesign","surfaces"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.6","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:47:59.664776955Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.6","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:57:24.767812294Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.6","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:02:36.191711626Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.6","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.8","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:27.006775235Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.6","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.9","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:17:50.444589022Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.6","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:48:00.220431554Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.6","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:48:00.733775080Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.6","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:33.601302775Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.6","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:48:01.338317557Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.6","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:47:44.351219027Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":330,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.6","author":"ubuntu","text":"Split out from the original all-in-one inspect bead to improve parallelism and reduce a planning bottleneck.","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:47:45Z"}]}
-{"id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","title":"robot-redesign/surfaces: add structured diagnostics and explainability drill-down across inspect surfaces","description":"Add structured diagnostics and explainability drill-down so operators can inspect why snapshot, status, digest, attention, and inspect views look the way they do. This task exists because recovery is faster and trust is higher when ntm can expose source degradation, cursor state, truncation, projection freshness, and incident or attention evidence directly from the shared model instead of from raw logs.","design":"The work should define focused inspect views or modes for source-health breakdown, projection-update status, replay-window and cursor diagnostics, bounded-output or truncation explanations, suppression or aggregation explanations, request-correlation or idempotency diagnostics, operator attention-state diagnostics such as why an item is snoozed, pinned, muted, resurfaced, or force-escalated, and incident or attention evidence summaries. It should decide which explanation handles are shown inline in summary surfaces and which details live only in deeper drill-down, while avoiding a new overview command or a generic debug dump. This bead should make explainability a disciplined part of the inspect family: targeted, machine-readable, and sourced from the shared projection model rather than ad hoc formatter text.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when the redesign can answer questions such as why is this section stale, why did this incident open, why is this cursor invalid or expired, why was this output truncated, why was this item suppressed or resurfaced, why is it pinned or snoozed, and which request or outcome this evidence belongs to through supported inspect surfaces with stable shared semantics.","notes":"This is about trust and debugging speed, not verbosity for its own sake. The diagnostics flow should shorten recovery loops for both machine and human operators.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-03-22T00:09:11.713088410Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T01:37:23.315332498Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["diagnostics","inspect","robot-redesign","surfaces"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.10","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:23:32.438181484Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.11","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:29:48.877332108Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.12","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:47:58.038207644Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.13","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:26:00.392438841Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.14","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:18.249287076Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:30.183341957Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.8","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:29.487800896Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.9","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:17:51.068802912Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:32.789431718Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:30.808813660Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:34.444587091Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:31.491786147Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:32.151803814Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:09:11.713088410Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:33.475003652Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:34.170842501Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":335,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","author":"ubuntu","text":"Watch-semantics follow-up: diagnostics must answer why no events are arriving, whether a stream is healthy-idle versus stalled, which filters are active, whether backpressure or boundedness suppressed delivery, and why a heartbeat or progress annotation did or did not appear.","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:49:02Z"},{"id":344,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","author":"ubuntu","text":"Historical-diagnostics follow-up: inspect surfaces must explain whether a historical answer came from replay or cached reconstruction, why history is partial or unavailable, which retention or boundedness rule limited the view, and how an operator pivots from a live incident summary into a recent as-of explanation without raw event archaeology.","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:28:15Z"},{"id":354,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","author":"ubuntu","text":"Sensitivity follow-up: diagnostics must explain not only why something is stale or prioritized, but also why content is visible, previewed, hashed, redacted, or withheld, including which disclosure rule or replay limit shaped the answer.","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:37:23Z"}]}
+{"id":"bd-j9jo3.6.6","title":"robot-redesign/surfaces: rationalize targeted inspect surfaces for work, coordination, quota, and incident drill-down","description":"Split the inspect-surface work so coordination-heavy drill-down does not stay entangled with session and agent drill-down. This task exists because work backlog, unread mail, reservation conflicts, handoffs, quota pressure, and incidents deserve a distinct operator-facing detail model from session/pane inspection.","design":"The work should define inspect views or modes for work items, coordination state, quota or health state, and incidents, including stable lookup keys, expected detail depth, how invalid or unsupported lookups are reported, and how these views are reached from snapshot and attention. It should also make clear where these detail surfaces stop, how they coordinate with the shared diagnostics flow for evidence, source-health causes, cursor or replay context, and incident reasoning, and why they do not become another dumping ground for raw subsystem output.

