+{"id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","title":"robot-redesign/surfaces: add structured diagnostics and explainability drill-down across inspect surfaces","description":"Add structured diagnostics and explainability drill-down so operators can inspect why snapshot, status, digest, attention, and inspect views look the way they do. This task exists because recovery is faster and trust is higher when ntm can expose source degradation, cursor state, truncation, projection freshness, and incident or attention evidence directly from the shared model instead of from raw logs.","design":"The work should define focused inspect views or modes for source-health breakdown, projection-update status, replay-window and cursor diagnostics, bounded-output or truncation explanations, suppression or aggregation explanations, request-correlation or idempotency diagnostics, operator attention-state diagnostics such as why an item is snoozed, pinned, muted, resurfaced, or force-escalated, and incident or attention evidence summaries. It should decide which explanation handles are shown inline in summary surfaces and which details live only in deeper drill-down, while avoiding a new overview command or a generic debug dump. This bead should make explainability a disciplined part of the inspect family: targeted, machine-readable, and sourced from the shared projection model rather than ad hoc formatter text.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when the redesign can answer questions such as why is this section stale, why did this incident open, why is this cursor invalid or expired, why was this output truncated, why was this item suppressed or resurfaced, why is it pinned or snoozed, and which request or outcome this evidence belongs to through supported inspect surfaces with stable shared semantics.","notes":"This is about trust and debugging speed, not verbosity for its own sake. The diagnostics flow should shorten recovery loops for both machine and human operators.","status":"closed","priori