 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.7.2","title":"robot-redesign/registry: drive capabilities, help, and schema output from the registry","description":"Refactor robot discovery surfaces so capabilities, help, and schema output are generated from the shared registry instead of bespoke logic. This task exists to make discovery trustworthy for both humans and machine consumers.","design":"The work should ensure ntm --robot-capabilities, ntm --robot-help, and schema-discovery surfaces reflect the same registry-backed truth about available commands, sections, diagnostics modes, schema IDs, options, transport coverage, request identity or idempotency support, attention-state controls, action-handoff expectations, and explanation capabilities or evidence handles. Checked-in schema artifacts should participate in this flow rather than living as dead documentation. This task should shrink the space for accidental mismatch between docs, code, and actual surface behavior.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when help, capabilities, and schema discovery are visibly registry-backed and remain aligned as new surfaces or schema versions are introduced, including the semantics that tell consumers how to retry safely, correlate later outcomes, and intentionally shape the attention loop.","notes":"Machine consumers should be able to trust discovery output instead of treating it as marketing copy.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":150,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:21.404153219Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:19.076583864Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["capabilities","registry","robot-redesign"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.7.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.10","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:23:33.009157839Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.7.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.11","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:29:49.4836149